With our mission to innovate and take bold steps forward in education as a leading education technology services provider, we are an entrepreneurially-minded organization looking to the future—but with more than a decade of experience and resources backing us up! We have a culture of  **Passion** ,  **Innovation**  and  **Teamwork** , and are full of ambitious people that, like you, support our commitment to putting people first. If you want to know more about us, be sure to check out Zovio.com.
  

  
**Job Description:**
  

  
**What You Will Do:**
  

  
• Create and update stored procedures, functions, views, reports (using Crystal Reports &amp; Excel), SQL jobs, and SSIS packages (SSRS is a plus)
  

  
•  Participate in all phases of the software development life-cycle - requirements, design, implementation, testing, release, maintenance
  

  
•  Implement projects focused on business workflows, automated systems, reporting, and data analysis.
  

  
•  Participate in collaborative work with DBA’s, Software Engineers, Business Analysts, Subject Matter Experts, and Project Managers to achieve software solutions
  

  
• Perform code reviews for peers, mentor/coach new hires and junior members of the team
  

  
•  Assist in process improvement initiatives
  

  
•  Assist external auditors, regulatory auditors and other 3rd parties as needed
  

  
•  Assist in company-wide compliance initiatives
  

  
• Both Managers and Employees must ensure on a weekly basis accurate and complete timecards for each day of the week. At the end of the pay period, each employee and his/her manager must confirm the accuracy of the records and approve the timecards. This includes ensuring that all requests for sick and vacation has been recorded and that all-time record entries are accurate.
  

  
**Minimum Requirements** :
  

  
Minimum 5+ years with the following technologies:
  

  
+ 5+ plus years of experience in database developer position
  
+ Solid analytical and troubleshooting skills
  
+ Solid logical and physical database design skills
  
+ Advanced Development level experience with T-SQL
  
+ In-depth knowledge of SQL Server (MySQL knowledge a plus)
  
+ Experienced with basic ETL processes using SSIS
  
+ Experienced with Stored procedure creation/debugging/optimization/tuning
  
+ Business process analysis
  
+ Data conversion
  
+ Flow-charting
  
+ Data Modeling, profiling and Analysis skills
  
+ Solid analytical and communicational skills
  
+ Good documentation and writing skills
  
+ Strong oral written communication skills
  

  
Relevant experience in following areas is a plus:
  

  
+ Campus Nexus Student Integration/OData Services
  
+ Integration development with REST/SOAP API
  

  
**Education:**
  

  
+ Bachelor’s degree with 5+ years related experience
  
+ Or Master’s in Computer science with 3+ years of related experience.
  

  
**Who you are:**
  

  
+ You want to share what you know and learn what you don’t
  
+ You don’t settle for good , you strive for great
  
+ You crave change, you embrace it
  
+ You are bold and challenge the traditional way of thinking, bring new ideas to the table
  

  
**Why Us?**
  

  
+ We’re an organization changing and shaping the lives of learnings across the country. Whether directly or indirectly, you’ll be helping make a real difference in the world.
  
+ Our environment and culture encourages collaboration, requires communication and rewards risk-taking.
  
+ We try hard to provide a good work life balance. We think we’re a great place to work that also allows you to have down time with friends and family.
  
