**Job Description:**
  

  
**About the Role:**
  

  
The Advising Enablement Specialist will help our advisors/coaches/specialists understand our solutions and train them on product features in the context of prospective and enrolled student challenges. The job will entail creating tools, resources, training and enablement content and delivering it to sales and customer success teams.
  

  
The Operations Development Team at Zovio is critical to fueling the company's growth by utilizing a variety of strategies to support new enrollments and retention.
  

  
**Primary Job Responsibilities:**
  

  
+ Create resources and tools to assist students and advisors with new enrollment and retention
  
+ Project management of all projects relative to Advising Enablement
  
+ Ensure strategic, tactical, and practical coordination between our clients, marketing, advising, and students
  
+ Communicate directly and indirectly with multiple departments to ensure consistency in advising efforts
  
+ Participate in various company initiatives and projects as requested
  

  
**Skills and Qualifications:**
  

  
+ Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience
  
+ 5 years + in sales, marketing or sales enablement/training capacity
  
+ Affinity for training and instructional design
  
+ Ability to work with multiple groups and cross level executive, managers, and individual contributors
  
+ Capacity to digest quickly complex content and break it down in simple learning experiences
  
+ Has demonstrated presentation, training, and coaching skills
  
+ Can be coached and welcomes coaching
  
+ Proficiency with the MS Office suite including in-depth knowledge of Outlook, Word, and Excel with the ability to pick up new systems and software easily
  

  
