**Job Description:**
  

  
**Position Summary:**
  

  
The  **Product Specialist**  position is a  **full-time**  employment opportunity. The  **Product Specialist**  will work to support and strengthen the bridges between our business departments and our technology department in order to ensure the best possible experience for our partner institutions’ students and strategic partners is delivered.  The  **Product Specialist**  is an entry-level role in our Product Delivery Organization and will learn to guide business and IT stakeholders to successful solution delivery. We are looking for an individual who is interested in product and software development, can analyze and articulate Higher Education business processes, and has a passion for delivering new products and services in a highly collaborative environment.
  

  
The best candidates are seeking a career in business leadership, interested in business service development and business processes modeling, and exceptional communicators.  We expect the  **Product Specialist**  to have knowledge of the practical use of various solutions including, but not limited to, Customer Relationship Management (like Salesforce.com); Student Information Systems (like CampusVue); and Learning Management Systems (like Canvas or Blackboard). The  **Product Specialist**  will work under the guidance of a Sr. Product Manager to analyze business capability change requests; identify business process gaps; align business capabilities with the IT services that serve the business users; report discovered technical debt, decompose desired business capabilities down to features and use cases; and take ownership of product change success. The ideal candidate will have an entrepreneurial spirit; be self-motivated; is willing to learn and collaborate; and is courageous and confident while being respectful of divergent opinions.
  

  
**Essential Job Duties:**
  

  
+ Manage small product enhancements and initiatives that are driven by business priorities and IT resource allocations
  
+ Collaborate with business and technical teams to maintain high-level product roadmaps in order to lead change
  
+ Define new business capabilities or changes to existing capabilities
  
+ Create and manage initiative, epic, or sprint definitions to manage detailed requirements
  
+ Decompose capabilities to features, use cases, user stories, and work instructions
  
+ Meet regularly with the business representatives to understand current and desired product capabilities performance and develop gap analyses for each change request
  
+ Keep the Director of the PMO advised of all work status through continual updates to our product backlogs and service offerings
  
+ Ensure business change requests are rationalized against our backlogs to avoid duplication of effort and conflicts in scheduling change
  
+ Assist with creating, maintaining and prioritizing the product backlog
  
+ Work with Sr. Product Managers to advocate your business areas’ backlog prioritization
  
+ Attend daily Scrums to communicate changes in priority and to assist in removing roadblocks
  
+ Remove roadblocks as reported by the Scrum Master on behalf of the delivery team
  
+ Ensure business is engaged daily in the delivery team activities to ensure testing completeness and work product acceptance at the end of each iteration
  
+ Address any change of scope with the Business Product and Service Owners, Enterprise PMO, BTS Product Delivery, and Project Managers.
  
+ Review and accept solution design documents to ensure proposed solutions meet business requirements and technical specifications
  

  
**Minimum Requirements:**
  

  
+ 2 years of experience with CRM solutions
  
+ 2 years of practical Scrum experience
  
+ Familiarity with JIRA Software or similar solutions to track tasks, build a backlog, create user stories, sprints, and other collateral and monitor status
  
+ Familiarity with Data Lakes, ODS, OLAP, OTP, and other common data and processing concepts
  
+ Ability to lead business requirements gathering sessions
  
+ Ability to prioritize items based on value and importance
  
+ Awareness of Agile delivery concepts
  
+ Ability to correctly write a User Story
  
+ Experience applying Agile principles and practices
  
+ Experience working with multiple teams
  
+ Ability to think and act strategically for all stakeholders
  
+ Possess strong verbal and written communication skills
  

  
**Preferred Qualifications:**
  

  
+ 1-2 years of experience with the Salesforce.com Platform
  
+ 1-2 years of practical Scrum experience
  
+ 1-2 years of practical, applied experience with JIRA Software to track tasks, build a backlog, create User Stories, sprints, and other collateral and monitor status
  
